results.occurrenceRemarks: Large Brown Spitting Cobra (Naja ashei), Adult, being moved back to it's cage after cleaning. This snake was collected in Watamu and kept at the Bio-Ken Snake Farm and snake venom research facility in Watamu, Kenya. This species is the world's largest spitting cobra, and was officially recognized as a new species distinct from the Black-Necked Spitting Cobra (Naja nigricollis) in 2007. Bio-Ken described and discovered the species and it is named after Bio-Ken founder and legendary snakeman James Ashe.
